properties.name: Cleveland Hopkins International Airport
properties.icon: amtrak
properties.description: The problem with trying to place a railroad station at Cleveland Hopkins is that there's no real good space for it. The east side of the mainline tracks are blocked by a large number of sidings, but the west side of the tracks are blocked by the Berea Freeway and the GCRTA tracks and yard. The Amtrak station's platforms would have to be narrow, positioned either side of the three through tracks, connected to parking and ticketing by a walkway bridge or tunnel.
